739
00:35:55.640 --> 00:35:58.280
I love how it looks.
I love the colours.

740
00:35:58.280 --> 00:36:00.560
I think those layers
are stunning.

741
00:36:00.560 --> 00:36:02.720
I think she's done
a really good job.

742
00:36:05.360 --> 00:36:07.440
Hello. Pat.

743
00:36:07.440 --> 00:36:11.520
I've made a prawn bisque
with a butter-poached prawn.

744
00:36:11.520 --> 00:36:13.360
some lightly smoked mussels.

745
00:36:13.360 --> 00:36:17.080
roasted fennel.
and fondant potatoes.

746
00:36:17.080 --> 00:36:19.480
This is very inviting.

747
00:36:19.480 --> 00:36:21.320
It is just amazing.

748
00:36:21.320 --> 00:36:25.840
Just smell it. The power of
the shells of the prawns.

749
00:36:25.840 --> 00:36:28.520
The mussels. The stock has
been done very well.

750
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:31.200
I think it's seasoned perfectly.

751
00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:34.040
ANDY: Nailed the brief. nailed
the conception of the dish.

752
00:36:34.040 --> 00:36:35.960
nailed the execution of
the dish.

753
00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:41.640
OLAOLU: It's a big risk
by doing a cake

754
00:36:41.640 --> 00:36:42.920
for an elimination cook.

755
00:36:42.920 --> 00:36:44.760
because cakes are
generally simple.

756
00:36:46.920 --> 00:36:49.600
But I'm hoping that the fact
that I have elevated it

757
00:36:49.600 --> 00:36:53.760
in terms of really swaying
the balance of the dish

758
00:36:53.760 --> 00:36:55.880
is enough to keep me safe
from being eliminated.

759
00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:57.120
ANDY: Olaolu.
Hello.

760
00:36:57.120 --> 00:36:58.320
Hey. Olaolu.

761
00:36:59.560 --> 00:37:00.960
Mmm!

762
00:37:00.960 --> 00:37:03.200
I've made a plantain cake
with some peanuts.

763
00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:06.360
It's inspired by
a Nigerian street food dish -

764
00:37:06.360 --> 00:37:07.640
boli and peanuts.

765
00:37:07.640 --> 00:37:10.200
How old were you when you were
smashing plantains

766
00:37:10.200 --> 00:37:11.520
and salted peanuts?

767
00:37:11.520 --> 00:37:13.760
I don't remember not doing it.
Oh. really?

768
00:37:13.760 --> 00:37:16.800
Probably from five. six. seven.
Oh. wow.

769
00:37:16.800 --> 00:37:19.120
You know. it's kind of just
roasting on the fire

770
00:37:19.120 --> 00:37:21.200
on the side of the street.
and you get it hot.

771
00:37:21.200 --> 00:37:23.560
So. it's a memory
that you've then channelled

772
00:37:23.560 --> 00:37:25.800
to basically create something.

773
00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:28.600
Yeah. For me. cooking is
a lot about creativity.

774
00:37:28.600 --> 00:37:31.840
And. so. well. Nigerians
don't really eat dessert.

775
00:37:31.840 --> 00:37:34.080
So. and I have
a big sweet tooth.

776
00:37:34.080 --> 00:37:36.120
so I wanted to kind of
turn that into a dessert.

777
00:37:36.120 --> 00:37:37.520
And that's how this came about.

778
00:37:37.520 --> 00:37:39.800
We'll taste now. Thanks. mate.
Good luck. Olaolu.

779
00:37:41.080 --> 00:37:43.440
What do you think. guys?
It's pretty cute.

780
00:37:43.440 --> 00:37:45.360
I think it looks nice.
JEAN-CHRISTOPHE: Yeah. it is.

781
00:37:45.360 --> 00:37:46.640
Yeah.

782
00:37:50.480 --> 00:37:52.400
Looks pretty good.
Nice.

783
00:37:52.400 --> 00:37:53.640
Very pleased.

784
00:38:11.360 --> 00:38:13.560
I absolutely love this.
It's good. huh?

785
00:38:13.560 --> 00:38:16.880
I was really concerned that
the cake was way too simple.

786
00:38:16.880 --> 00:38:20.560
but the texture
is just impeccable.

787
00:38:21.640 --> 00:38:25.200
I think the cake is
absolutely epic.

788
00:38:26.640 --> 00:38:29.560
It's lovely. It's gentle.

789
00:38:29.560 --> 00:38:33.560
And it has a bit of intensity
from the spice.

790
00:38:33.560 --> 00:38:35.600
It's just perfect.

791
00:38:36.800 --> 00:38:41.560
This cake. to me. is like
carrot cake and banana bread

792
00:38:41.560 --> 00:38:43.920
met at Christmas
and had an overachieving child.

793
00:38:43.920 --> 00:38:45.520
(LAUGHS)

794
00:38:45.520 --> 00:38:47.800
It has that beautiful
spice mix through it.

795
00:38:47.800 --> 00:38:50.080
and then you get these little
sweet. tangy pockets

796
00:38:50.080 --> 00:38:51.720
of that lime syrup.

797
00:38:51.720 --> 00:38:53.800
Also. that Chantilly.

798
00:38:53.800 --> 00:38:58.640
It's so light and fluffy.
and salted so perfectly.

799
00:38:58.640 --> 00:39:00.760
Plus the crunch
and that extra bit of salt

800
00:39:00.760 --> 00:39:04.360
from those quite heavily
toasted peanuts.

801
00:39:04.360 --> 00:39:07.400
It's a really delicious
flavour combination.

802
00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:08.600
This is hard to do.

803
00:39:08.600 --> 00:39:10.680
The fact that he can
really sit there

804
00:39:10.680 --> 00:39:12.880
and take this memory
and distil it into

805
00:39:12.880 --> 00:39:17.400
a very simple cake and anglaise.
but then have the smarts to go.

806
00:39:17.400 --> 00:39:19.160
"I'm gonna do this.
this and this to it

807
00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:23.480
"to really. really bring it back
to a MasterChef-worthy palate."

808
00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:26.440
Dynamite. mate. Dynamite.
I'm super stoked for him.

809
00:39:26.440 --> 00:39:29.080
I think we should be waiting
for a long run with him.

810
00:39:34.480 --> 00:39:36.760
HANNAH: The end of this cook
was a blur.

811
00:39:36.760 --> 00:39:37.760
Hannah.
Hi. Hannah.

812
00:39:37.760 --> 00:39:39.160
JEAN-CHRISTOPHE: How are you?

813
00:39:39.160 --> 00:39:41.000
Hello.

814
00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:43.080
I'm not feeling super confident
in my dish.

815
00:39:43.080 --> 00:39:46.040
but I'm hoping it's good enough
to get me through.

816
00:39:56.080 --> 00:39:57.120
Hello.

817
00:39:57.120 --> 00:39:58.120
Hello.
Hi. Hannah.

818
00:39:58.120 --> 00:40:00.040
How are you?

819
00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:02.400
I've made you a sticky date
pudding

820
00:40:02.400 --> 00:40:04.640
with a ginger crumb
and a ginger ice-cream.

821
00:40:04.640 --> 00:40:06.640
and an orange butterscotch
sauce.

822
00:40:28.960 --> 00:40:30.920
I'm troubled.
You're troubled?

823
00:40:30.920 --> 00:40:32.800
Mm.
What are you troubled with?

824
00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:36.760
The pudding itself is lovely.

825
00:40:36.760 --> 00:40:38.960
It's really well cooked.
it's nice and moist.

826
00:40:38.960 --> 00:40:41.720
but the butterscotch
is not a butterscotch.

827
00:40:41.720 --> 00:40:44.680
She's cooked her orange juice
down so much

828
00:40:44.680 --> 00:40:47.000
that it's got this kind
of marmaladey flavour.

829
00:40:47.000 --> 00:40:49.280
It's like an emulsion butter.

830
00:40:49.280 --> 00:40:51.920
Oh. yeah.
It's nothing toffee.

831
00:40:51.920 --> 00:40:55.280
I just didn't use the sauce.
and I used the ice-cream.

832
00:40:55.280 --> 00:40:58.600
which was very ginger forward.
which I really enjoyed.

833
00:40:58.600 --> 00:41:01.440
I love the ice-cream. I
absolutely adore the ice-cream.

834
00:41:01.440 --> 00:41:03.200
It is the best thing
on that plate for me.

835
00:41:03.200 --> 00:41:04.440
It is so delicious.

836
00:41:04.440 --> 00:41:07.520
But do you think the ice-cream
is good enough to save her?

837
00:41:07.520 --> 00:41:08.960
Yeah. I don't know.

838
00:41:17.520 --> 00:41:19.760
Today was an
emotional challenge.

839
00:41:21.040 --> 00:41:24.000
You shared your family
traditions with us.

840
00:41:24.000 --> 00:41:26.360
so we know these dishes.

841
00:41:26.360 --> 00:41:28.520
they were cherished memories
on the plate.

842
00:41:28.520 --> 00:41:31.400
Thank you for sharing that
with us. Well done.

843
00:41:37.360 --> 00:41:39.160
A big effort from everybody.

844
00:41:39.160 --> 00:41:41.200
But there was one dish

845
00:41:41.200 --> 00:41:45.760
that made us totally feel
like one big happy family.

846
00:41:45.760 --> 00:41:49.080
And that belonged to you. Lydia!

847
00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:53.640
(CHEERING)

848
00:42:00.320 --> 00:42:06.080
Lydia. that avgolemono was like
the biggest hug on a cold day.

849
00:42:06.080 --> 00:42:08.600
Literally. every single one
of us was slurping

850
00:42:08.600 --> 00:42:10.520
straight out of the bowl
and we could not speak.

851
00:42:10.520 --> 00:42:13.360
We were just diving into
the lemony chickeny goodness.

852
00:42:13.360 --> 00:42:15.840
It was really. really
spectacular.

853
00:42:15.840 --> 00:42:17.280
Thank you.

854
00:42:17.280 --> 00:42:18.920
Congratulations...
Thank you. they were...

855
00:42:18.920 --> 00:42:20.680
..you are safe.

856
00:42:20.680 --> 00:42:25.080
However. this is an elimination

857
00:42:25.080 --> 00:42:28.800
and. sadly. someone will be
going home today.

858
00:42:30.240 --> 00:42:32.120
SOFIA: There were two dishes
that missed the mark.

859
00:42:33.960 --> 00:42:36.600
If I call your name.
please step forward.

860
00:42:38.760 --> 00:42:39.760
Bella...

861
00:42:44.800 --> 00:42:46.120
.. and Hannah.

862
00:42:50.880 --> 00:42:53.040
Hannah. your sauce
was unpleasant.

863
00:42:53.040 --> 00:42:55.160
OK. Yeah.

864
00:42:55.160 --> 00:42:56.960
Bella.

865
00:42:56.960 --> 00:42:59.640
while we really admire
your ambition.

866
00:42:59.640 --> 00:43:01.200
time got the better of you.

867
00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:03.800
There were flaws in
most of your elements.

868
00:43:03.800 --> 00:43:05.040
I'm so sorry...

869
00:43:06.640 --> 00:43:08.320
.. but we have to say goodbye...

870
00:43:10.480 --> 00:43:11.720
.. Bella.

871
00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:25.000
Bella. we absolutely loved
having you

872
00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:26.680
as part of
the MasterChef family.

873
00:43:30.400 --> 00:43:33.840
Your cooking is
well beyond your years.

874
00:43:35.800 --> 00:43:37.240
What is it about this experience

875
00:43:37.240 --> 00:43:39.760
that will stay with you
the most?

876
00:43:39.760 --> 00:43:42.800
Um... cooking with
these amazing bunch

877
00:43:42.800 --> 00:43:45.560
of people has just been
so inspiring.

878
00:43:45.560 --> 00:43:47.120
Um. yeah. being able to. like.

879
00:43:47.120 --> 00:43:49.440
bounce ideas off everyone
and just be with people

880
00:43:49.440 --> 00:43:51.360
that share that same passion.

881
00:43:51.360 --> 00:43:54.920
Um. yeah. it's something that
I can't take for granted.

882
00:43:54.920 --> 00:43:56.960
Um. and I've enjoyed
every moment.

883
00:43:56.960 --> 00:44:00.480
Bella. I just wanted to say.

884
00:44:00.480 --> 00:44:04.240
your ambition. your tenacity.
your grit. your determination.

885
00:44:04.240 --> 00:44:10.720
your ability to just push
through under extreme pressure.

886
00:44:10.720 --> 00:44:13.960
you are one of
a handful of people

887
00:44:13.960 --> 00:44:18.040
that have those attributes
in absolute spades.

888
00:44:19.200 --> 00:44:20.800
That means a lot.

889
00:44:20.800 --> 00:44:23.920
Bella. I'm so broken-hearted
for you right now.

890
00:44:26.760 --> 00:44:29.720
You're so young and you have
so much talent.

891
00:44:32.280 --> 00:44:33.720
I know you're going to
be a superstar.

892
00:44:33.720 --> 00:44:34.840
and I want you to promise me

893
00:44:34.840 --> 00:44:38.520
that you're not going to
let this moment define you.

894
00:44:38.520 --> 00:44:40.880
It's what you actually do
after this. yeah?

895
00:44:40.880 --> 00:44:42.920
Yeah. Yeah.

896
00:44:42.920 --> 00:44:44.240
Come and give us a hug.

897
00:44:47.880 --> 00:44:50.360
I've learned so much
from this experience.

898
00:44:50.360 --> 00:44:53.880
and I am proud of the way
that I've showed up every day

899
00:44:53.880 --> 00:44:55.960
in this competition
and pushed myself.

900
00:44:57.120 --> 00:44:59.880
You are a younger version
of Mary Berry.

901
00:44:59.880 --> 00:45:02.240
(LAUGHS)

902
00:45:02.240 --> 00:45:03.960
All the best to you.
Don't give up.

903
00:45:03.960 --> 00:45:06.480
Poh made me promise that
this is only the beginning.

904
00:45:06.480 --> 00:45:08.680
and I'm going to stick to
that promise

905
00:45:08.680 --> 00:45:12.040
because I want to share the food
I love with so many people.

906
00:45:12.040 --> 00:45:14.280
and I'm going to find a way
to do that.

907
00:45:14.280 --> 00:45:18.880
Give it up for Bella. everybody!

908
00:45:18.880 --> 00:45:22.000
(CHEERING)

909
00:45:28.040 --> 00:45:30.760
ANNOUNCER: Next week on
MasterChef Australia...

910
00:45:30.760 --> 00:45:34.200
Please give it up
for Catherine Zhang!

911
00:45:35.720 --> 00:45:37.720
Victoria Minell!

912
00:45:37.720 --> 00:45:39.080
Khanh Ong!

913
00:45:40.160 --> 00:45:42.720
